properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued February 5 at 9:23PM EST until February 7 at 3:00AM EST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Minor coastal flooding expected with peak water levels of
2 to 3 feet above ground around the time of high tide on
Thursday afternoon and early Friday morning.

* WHERE...Coastal Jefferson and Coastal Wakulla Counties.

* WHEN...From 10 AM Thursday to 3 AM EST Friday.

* IMPACTS...At 2 feet above ground, water floods Mashes Sands
Beach Road and low lying areas around Panacea. In St Marks, Old
Fort Road will flood. At 3 feet above ground, water will begin
to flood Riverside Drive in St Marks.
properties.instruction:
If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be
closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone
property.

NWSheadline: COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM THURSDAY TO 3 AM EST FRIDAY
